# Magnetic Tape

## Description

The Magnetic Tape is a data structure that simulates the behavior of a magnetic tape, used in early computing for data storage. It consists of a linear sequence of blocks, each capable of storing data. Data can be written to and read from the tape, which maintains the First-In-First-Out (FIFO) order for data retrieval. In this implementation, a circular queue structure is used to emulate the behavior of a magnetic tape.

## Functionality

This Magnetic Tape implementation provides the following operations:

- `initMagneticTape(size_t capacity)`: Initializes a new Magnetic Tape with the specified capacity.
- `writeBlock(MagneticTape *tape, const uint8_t data[DEFAULT_TAPE_BLOCK_SIZE])`: Writes a block of data to the Magnetic Tape.
- `readBlock(MagneticTape *tape, uint8_t data[DEFAULT_TAPE_BLOCK_SIZE])`: Reads a block of data from the Magnetic Tape.
- `printTape(MagneticTape *tape, const char *restrict format)`: Prints all blocks of the Magnetic Tape.
- `destroyMagneticTape(MagneticTape *tape)`: Destroys the Magnetic Tape and frees the allocated memory.
